hellkite (HEL-kyt) noun

   An extremely cruel person.

[From Middle English hell (a place of misery) + kite (a person who preys
on others).]

   "So the old hellkite, Elemmakil's ex-wife Adalgar, is in for a surprise
   visit in the middle of her holiday dinner."
   Gilly daughter of Gerda, One Cold Night of Broken Neon and Shady Dives,
   The Ring of Doom & Farmer Maggot Deliveries, Bill & Lugdush® 6, 2000.

